[size=18pt][color=#6B46C1][b]What Makes Q-NarwhalKnight Different[/b][/color][/size]
[hr]

Every major blockchain today - Bitcoin, Ethereum, Solana, Cardano - relies on elliptic curve cryptography (ECDSA, Ed25519) that [b]Shor's algorithm can break in polynomial time[/b] on a sufficiently powerful quantum computer. This isn't science fiction:

[list]
[li][b]IBM Quantum Heron (2024):[/b] 1,121 physical qubits with record-low error rates[/li]
[li][b]Google Willow (2024):[/b] Demonstrated quantum error correction below threshold[/li]
[li][b]NIST FIPS 203/204/205 (2024):[/b] Post-quantum algorithm standards finalized[/li]
[li][b]NSA CNSA 2.0:[/b] Mandates post-quantum algorithms for classified systems by 2035[/li]
[li][b]"Harvest Now, Decrypt Later":[/b] Nation-states are already storing encrypted traffic for future quantum decryption[/li]
[/list]

The $3+ trillion crypto market cap is sitting on an unhedged existential risk. Q-NarwhalKnight is the [b]only production-ready Layer 1[/b] that has already completed the post-quantum transition.


