[size=18pt][color=#6B46C1][b]Recent Engineering: Decentralization Hardening (February 2026)[/b][/color][/size]
[hr]

In the final push toward mainnet, we completed a comprehensive decentralization and money integrity audit. Five critical areas were identified and resolved:

[b][color=#EF4444]1. State Root Computation (P0 - Fixed)[/color][/b]

Block headers now contain a real SHA3-256 state root computed over all transaction IDs. This enables any node to independently verify block integrity. The upgrade is height-gated through our consensus upgrade system, meaning historical blocks remain valid while new blocks carry cryptographic state proofs.

[b][color=#EF4444]2. DEX Swaps On-Chain (P0 - Fixed)[/color][/b]

Previously, DEX swaps were executed locally but not included in blocks propagated to other nodes. Pool reserves could diverge between peers. Now, swap transactions are included in blocks via the production mempool, and all nodes process incoming swap transactions from P2P blocks. A deduplication mechanism prevents double-crediting when a locally-executed swap arrives in a block.

[b][color=#EF4444]3. P2P Balance Update Validation (P0 - Fixed)[/color][/b]

P2P balance updates now carry block evidence fields (block_hash, tx_index) to prevent unsubstantiated balance inflation. Rate limits were tightened from 50,000 to 2,000 updates/node/minute. An aggregate amount cap of 100 QUG/node/minute prevents supply inflation attacks. Unknown peers are rejected unless they're verified bootstrap nodes.

[b][color=#F59E0B]4. Bootstrap Decentralization (P1 - Fixed)[/color][/b]

The network no longer depends on just 2 hardcoded bootstrap nodes. Peer discovery now uses 6 sources in priority order:
[list]
[li]Environment variables (Q_BOOTSTRAP_PEERS)[/li]
[li]Config file (config.toml in data directory)[/li]
[li]Cached peers (known_peers.json - persists top 20 across restarts)[/li]
[li]DNS bootstrap (bootstrap.quillon.xyz TXT records)[/li]
[li]Hardcoded defaults (always available as fallback)[/li]
[/list]

[b][color=#F59E0B]5. Token Deployment Authentication (P2 - Fixed)[/color][/b]

Token deployment now requires wallet authentication, pre-checks balance before execution, and enforces a rate limit of 5 deployments per wallet per hour. No more anonymous token spam.


