[b]Why time-based halvings?[/b] Traditional blockchains couple emission to block height. Protocol improvements that produce faster blocks [i]accelerate[/i] the halving schedule, making tokenomics unpredictable. QUG halvings occur on fixed calendar dates regardless of block production rate. Faster blocks = more utility, same scarcity.

[b]Fair launch.[/b] No premine. No ICO. No VC allocation. VDF mining levels the playing field - your laptop contributes meaningfully. The 0.5% dev fee is the only team allocation.


